        <div class="top-wrap laws">
            <div class="dancing-cursive">
                <h2> Article I     </h2>   
                <h3> Incorporation </h3>            
            </div>
            <ol>
                <li>
                    The name of this organization shall be “Charleston Area Justice Ministry (CAJM)”.
                </li>
                <li>
                    CAJM shall be a non-profit corporation, established in accordance with section 501 (c)(3) of the Tax Code of the Internal Revenue Service and the laws of the State of South Carolina.
                </li>
                <li>
                    Authority is vested in the Annual Assembly (“Annual Assembly”), which is the ultimate decision-making body for the organization which delegates authority and responsibility between meetings to the Leadership Senate.
                </li>               
            </ol>
        </div>

        <div class="top-wrap laws">
            <div class="dancing-cursive">
                <h2> Article II </h2>   
                <h3> Affiliation with Direct Action and Research Training Center, Inc. (DART) </h3>            
            </div>
            <ol>
                <li>
                    CAJM shall maintain an affiliation with the Direct Action and Research Training Center, Inc. (DART). 
                </li>
                <li>
                    CAJM shall rely on DART to provide training and consulting support for CAISC leaders and to recruit and train new organizing staff.  
                </li>           
            </ol>
        </div>

        <div class="top-wrap laws">
            <div class="dancing-cursive">
                <h2> Article III </h2>   
                <h3> Membership  </h3>            
            </div>
            <ol>          
                <li> 
                    CAJM shall be an organization of congregations or community organizations.
                </li>
                <li>
                    Congregations become member organizations of CAJM after subscribing to the following covenant: _______ (name of the congregation), enters into a covenant with CAJM for the purpose of more successfully practicing our values in our community by:
                    <ol>
                        <li> Building a Justice Ministry Network in our congregation; </li>  
                        <li> Engaging in a listening process, training leaders, developing solutions, and taking action to improve community conditions;  </li> 
                        <li> Accepting responsibility for the financial health of the organization by contributing annually and by supporting CAJM fundraising efforts; </li>
                        <li> Voicing the concerns of the members of our congregations during Assemblies and fully supporting the agreed upon goals; and finally... </li>
                        <li> Selecting leaders (Justice Ministry Team members) from our congregation to attend all CAJM Leadership Senate meetings. </li>
                    </ol>
                </li> 
                <li>
                    Voting rights of member congregations at the Annual Assembly, Leadership Senate and Justice Ministry Team Assemblies shall depend upon the payment of dues in a timely manner.
                </li>     
            </ol>
        </div>

        <div class="top-wrap laws">
            <div class="dancing-cursive">
                <h2> Article IV </h2>   
                <h3> Membership  </h3>            
            </div>
            <ol>
                <li> All powers derive from and ultimate authority is invested in the Annual Assembly including the authority to: 
                    <ol>
                        <li> Adopt policies, set issue priorities,  and authorize formation of issue/action committees; </li>
                        <li> Elect the officers and Nominating Committee of CAJM; </li>
                        <li> Amend this constitution in accordance with Article XII; and, </li>
                        <li> Act on any other business of the organization properly brought before it. </li>
                    </ol>
                </li>  
                <li> The Annual Assembly shall meet at least once a year on a date selected by the CAJM Leadership Senate.  Meetings of the Annual Assembly may be called at any time by the Leadership Senate.  Three-week’s written notice shall be given of any called meeting.</li>
                <li> Each member congregation shall send delegates to the Annual Meeting. Each member congregation shall be expected to send delegations composed of Justice Ministry Team and Justice Ministry Network Members. 
                    <ol>
                        <li> Only delegates who are present at the Annual Meeting shall have the right to vote. Each delegate present shall be entitled to one vote. A delegate shall represent only one organization. </li>
                        <li> The Annual Assembly, excepting those delegations involved in any dispute regarding seat, voice or vote, shall, by a simple majority of voting members present, be the final judge in determining the seating of delegates and alternates. </li>
                    </ol>
                </li> 
                <li> Notice of any Annual Meeting, including the agenda, shall be published to all member congregations at least two weeks prior to the meeting. </li> 
                <li> The delegates present at any properly convened Annual Assembly shall constitute a quorum provided that at least one-half (1/2) of the member congregations have a delegate present. </li> 
                <li> The Co-Presidents shall call the Annual Assembly to order and preside over the Assembly. </li>
            </ol>
        </div>        

        <div class="top-wrap laws">
            <div class="dancing-cursive">
                <h2> Article V   </h2>   
                <h3> Membership  </h3>            
            </div>
            <ol>
                <li> CAJM staff shall consist of a Lead Organizer and other Organizer(s).  Administrative personnel may also be employed. </li>
                <li> The Lead Organizer shall be accountable to the Board of Directors. </li>
                <li> The primary responsibilities of the Lead Organizer shall be as follow: 
                    <ol>
                        <li> Hire, supervise, mentor, and evaluate other staff employed by CAJM; </li>
                        <li> Function as the primary liaison between  CAJM and DART; </li>
                        <li> Regularly seek out and build relationships with new leaders and facilitate bringing in new congregations; </li>
                        <li>  Identify potential sources of financial support; </li>
                        <li> Ensure that all government and funding reports are completed in a timely fashion; </li>
                        <li> Ensure that financial records are accurate and current; </li>
                        <li> Develop and maintain a working knowledge of the issues, challenges, and local economic and political environment; and, </li>
                        <li> Advise the Leadership Senate, the Board of Directors and committees. </li>
                    </ol>
                </li> 
            </ol>   
        </div>        

        <div class="top-wrap laws">
            <div class="dancing-cursive">
                <h2> Article VI  </h2>   
                <h3> Officers and Board of Directors  </h3>            
            </div>
            <ol>
                <li> The Officers and the nine at Large members shall serve as the Board of Directors. The primary responsibilities of the members of the Board of Directors shall be to address the issues chosen by the Annual Assembly and communicate information from the Board meetings to the member congregations and information from the member congregations to the Board. The chief functions shall be as follow:
                    <ol>
                        <li> Review the CAJM Assembly agendas and recommendations and plan for good attendance; </li>
                        <li> Adopt the annual operating budget and secure and oversee the financial well-being of CAJM; </li>
                        <li> Accept new member organizations; </li>
                        <li> Act on the recommendations from the Membership Committee regarding applications of organizations applying for membership in CAJM; </li>
                        <li> Implement the priorities adopted by the Annual Assembly; </li>
                        <li>  Communicate information regarding CAJM operations and issues to member congregations and represent congregational interests and concerns at Board meetings; </li>
                        <li> Evaluate the CAJM ’s performance and accomplishments; </li>
                        <li> Adopt a dues structure for the organization; and, </li>
                        <li> Approve the employment of a Lead Organizer and establish guidelines for the evaluation of that person’s work. </li>
                    </ol>
                </li>
                <li> The Board of Directors shall meet at least six times per year. </li>
                <li> The Co-Presidents may convene special meetings of the Board of Directors. There shall be at least seven (7) days notice given to all Board members by mail/email or by phone. Special meetings must be called for stated, specific special business. </li>
                <li> Eight members of the Board shall be required to constitute a quorum for the Board of Directors. Participation in Board of Directors meetings may be by telephone or Skype when necessary. </li>
                <li> The officers of CAJM shall be: 
                    <ol> 
                        <li> Co-Presidents (two), who shall be spokespeople for CAJM chair all CAJM meetings, including Assemblies, Senate meetings and Board meetings, and carry out all the other normal functions of president.  The two Co-Presidents shall reflect the diversity of the organization and may be clergy or laypersons.  The Co-Presidents will serve staggered two year terms; </li>
                        <li> Vice-president, who shall assist the Co-Presidents as directed and in their absence act in their stead.  The Vice-president will be elected for one term as Vice-President; </li>
                        <li> Secretary, who shall record the proceedings of the Executive Committee, Assemblies, Leadership Senate and meetings of the Board of Directors.  The Secretary will be elected for a one year term; </li>
                        <li> Communications Officer, who shall be responsible for writing and posting notices and communications as directed by Co-Presidents and the Board of Directors, for providing notice of all meetings as set forth in this Constitution and Bylaws, for overseeing CAJM’s web presence and for developing media contacts.  The Communications Officer will be elected for a one year term; </li>
                        <li> Treasurer, who shall ensure that financial records are maintained in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles for not-for-profit organizations, submit a written financial report to the Board of Directors at the first meeting following the end of the previous quarter, and a full report to the Annual Assembly. The Treasurer shall submit all financial records annually for audit by the Finance Committee and for external audit when requested by the Board of Directors. The Treasurer will be elected for a one year term; and </li>
                        <li> Development Officer,  who shall oversee all funds collected by CAJM, monitor the payment of dues from member organizations, assist staff in membership recruitment, provide leadership in the development of corporate support of CAJM and assist in the formulation of fundraising strategies.  The Development Officer will be elected for a one year term. </li>
                    </ol>
                </li>
                <li> Nine At-Large members of the Board of Directors shall be elected at the Annual Assembly for one year terms. (The first year that the at-large members are elected five shall be elected to two year terms.) </li>
                <li> The slate of officers and at-large Board members shall be presented by the Nominating Committee at least three weeks prior to the Annual Assembly and elected by a majority vote at the Annual Assembly. The Nominating Committee shall also nominate three at large members to serve on the Nominating Committee for the next year.  The Nominating Committee shall nominate one qualified candidate for each office. Additional nominations may be offered provided that the nominee is supported by ten (10) signatures of delegates from at least five (5) member congregations and presented to the chairperson of the nominating committee one week prior to the Annual Assembly. The nominating committee shall consist of the current co-presidents and three at large members elected by the prior annual assembly. </li>
                <li> All candidates nominated by the nominating committee shall be members of a member organization and the slate of candidates shall reflect the rich diversity of the organization.  Candidates for any position may be clergy or lay persons. </li>
                <li> Should an office become vacant, the Board of Directors shall have the power to recommend an acting successor to serve until the next Annual Assembly, whose appointment shall be ratified by the Leadership Senate at its next meeting. Full year vacancies shall be filled by the regular nomination process. </li>
                <li> Prior to the assumption of office, all Board Members shall take the following oath: I, ___________________ , do hereby solemnly affirm to uphold the Constitution and By-Laws of CAJM  and to perform all duties as required by the Constitution and Bylaws and as mandated by the Annual Assembly.</li>
                <li> The Co-Presidents and Vice-President are limited to one term but may be elected to serve in another position.  All other offices can be elected for a second term.  Persons who have served their full allowed term(s) may be nominated for the same Board position after an absence from that position for one year. </li>
            </ol>
        </div>

